lamic/imran#name-term\",\"name\":\"Imran\",\"description\":\"Prosperity\"},\"articleSection\":\"Name Meaning\",\"keywords\":\"Imran meaning, Imran origin, Arabic linguistics, Islamic names, pronunciation, lucky number, cultural context\",\"wordCount\":500,\"citation\":{\"@type\":\"CreativeWork\",\"name\":\"NameVerse — Cultural Name Knowledge Base\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\"}}42:[\"$\",\"$L3e\",null,{\"id\":\"scholarly-article-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$48\"}}]\n49:T1f9a,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What does Imran mean?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The islamic boy name Imran translates to \\\"Prosperity, Long-lived, Name of a Prophet's Father\\\" from its Arabic roots. This meaning reflects the cultural values embedded in islamic naming traditions.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the origin of the name Imran?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Historically, Imran emerges from Arabic cultural background and is attested in English, Urdu, Arabic, Pashto, Hindi. The islamic naming tradition preserves this name for its meaningful linguistic origins.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is Imran a boy, girl, or unisex name?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The name Imran is listed as Male in islamic naming records. Parents should note that gender classification of names can differ by region and cultural context.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How do you pronounce Imran?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The correct pronunciation of Imran is \\\"im-RAN\\\", represented phonetically as /ɪmˈrɑːn/. Understanding the Arabic pronunciation helps capture the name's authentic sound.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the phonetic transcription of Imran?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Phonetically, Imran is transcribed as /ɪmˈrɑːn/. The IPA representation helps linguists and language learners capture the name's authentic Arabic pronunciation.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the lucky associations for Imran?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"For Imran, Arabic naming lore specifies lucky number 1, Monday as the auspicious day, Blue, Gold as favourable colors, and Topaz as the protective stone. Such details are traditional rather than scientific.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the numerology of Imran?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"In numerology, Imran corresponds to the number 1, with Monday as a significant day, and Topaz as a related gemstone. Numerological analysis assigns meaning based on letter values and phonetic structure.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What personality traits are associated with Imran?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The islamic name Imran is believed to embody Loyal, Spiritual, Noble, Honest. Such personality associations stem from the name's meaning and its cultural usage patterns.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the cultural significance of Imran?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Within islamic tradition, Imran carries cultural weight beyond its literal meaning. Its Arabic origins and definition \\\"Prosperity, Long-lived, Name of a Prophet's Father\\\" position it as a name that connects heritage to contemporary identity. Imran is a name deeply rooted in Islamic culture and carries a rich heritage. It is not only the name of the revered prophet's father but is also used as a given name for boys in various Muslim communities around the world. The name represents strong roots, noble lineage, and prosperity, making it a proud and meaningful name for many families.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the spiritual meaning of Imran?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"In spiritual terms, Imran carries the meaning \\\"Prosperity, Long-lived, Name of a Prophet's Father\\\". islamic sources elaborate that symbolizes spiritual leadership, generational blessings, and family honor — a name tied to prophetic ancestry.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What names are similar to Imran?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"If Imran appeals to you, consider isa, iqrit, inga, id. These names echo Arabic naming traditions and offer related meanings or sounds.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What category does Imran belong to?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The name Imran falls under the \\\"Islamic\\\" category within islamic naming classifications. This categorisation helps parents find names that match their thematic preferences.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How is Imran written in Arabic?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The Arabic equivalent of Imran is \\\"عمرを持つ、繁栄する、高齢者\\\". Such translations show how the name transcends linguistic boundaries while retaining its fundamental meaning.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How is Imran written in English?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"In English, the name Imran is written as \\\"Long-lived, prosperous, rich\\\". This rendering adapts the name's sound and meaning to english script and phonetic conventions.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How is Imran written in Urdu?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The Urdu form of Imran is \\\"عمریں رکھنے والا، بڑھیا، خوشحال\\\". Cross-script representations like this demonstrate how the name maintains its identity across different writing systems.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-06-30T18:30:00+05:00\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}}]}43:[\"$\",\"$L3e\",null,{\"id\":\"faq-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$49\"}}]\n44:[\"$\",\"$L3e\",null,{\"id\":\"breadcrumb-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Islamic Names\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/religion/islamic/1\\\"},{\\\"@